title: Employment agencies; turnover, 2010=100
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: employment-agencies-turnover-2010100
notes:
This table provides information on turnover developments in the Temporary employment sector (SIC 2008 code 78). The data can be divided by a number of branches according to Statistics Netherlands' Standard Industrial Classification of all Economic Activities 2008 (SIC 2008). Job pool companies (SIC code 78203) are not included in the survey. These companies account for only a very small part (1 percent) of total temporary employment sector (SIC code 78). The results are expressed in index figures with base year 2010. Changes on the same period in the previous year are also published.

Data available from 1st quarter 2005.

Status of the figures
(Seasonally adjusted) Figures on all quarters of 2014 are provisional, the remainder are definite. Seasonally adjusted figures are recalculated every time a new period is added. This may affect figures of previous periods.

Changes as of 27 February 2015:
Figures of the fourth quarter and the year 2014 have been added and figures from three quarters preceding can have been adjusted.

When will new figures be published?
Statistics Netherlands usually publishes the first results 60 days after the report quarter. In the periods after this, figures may be adjusted as increased response becomes available. Definite (seasonally adjusted) figures become available approximately eight months after the reporting period. 

Once definite figures have been published, Statistics Netherlands only adjusts them if significant corrections are necessary.
